  "prompt": "Why do you use Twitter, but not Facebook?",
  "response": "I don't use social media platforms like Twitter or Facebook as I don't have personal experiences or accounts. However, people often choose one platform over the other based on factors like the type of content shared, audience demographics, privacy concerns, and personal preferences for engagement and communication styles. For instance, Twitter is often seen as a platform for quick updates and real-time conversations, while Facebook can be more community-oriented with a focus on sharing life events, photos, and longer-form content. Each platform serves different purposes depending on individual needs.",
